My issue looks similar to #48083 but as I've been told **it is about caching generated assembly,** not the generator itself. But I can't figure out what's going wrong.

A have 4 projects:
* ClientApi - references `Grpc.Tools` and contains definitions of services in proto-files
* Generator - generates a class with a list of all GRPC-clients found in `ReferencedAssemblySymbols`
* Implementation - references `Generator` and `ClientApi`
* Program - references `Implementation` and uses generated class

So I have a project with some services and clients generated by `grpc` and I want to autogenerate a class with all grpc-clients as properties.

In `ClientApi` project I have this proto:
```
syntax = "proto3";
package client_api;

service TestService {
    rpc Method1(Message) returns (Message) {}
}

message Message {}
```

In `Implementation` project I can see that this class is successfully generated by my generator:
```cs
using ClientApi;
using Grpc.Core;

#nullable enable
namespace GeneratedApi;

public partial class GeneratedApiBase
{
    public TestService.TestServiceClient TestServiceClient {get; set;}
}
```

But if I try to use it in `Program`
```cs
using GeneratedApi;

Console.WriteLine(new GeneratedApiBase().TestServiceClient);
```
there is this error:
```
Program.cs(3, 42): [CS1061] 'GeneratedApiBase' does not contain a definition for 'TestServiceClient' and no accessible extension method 'TestServiceClient' accepting a first argument of type 'GeneratedApiBase' could be found (are you missing a using directive or an assembly reference?)
```


Manually building projects one-by-one helps to overcome this issue, but then it fails again after adding new service to proto-file.
It looks like as if  `ClientApi` is cached somewhere in a state without files generated by GRPC, and SorceGenerator fails to understand that the appear at some point. 

Here is a [sample_solution.zip](https://github.com/dotnet/roslyn/files/10380574/Program.zip), where
1. building solution will fail
2. rebuilding `Implementation` without dependencies, and building `Program` after that will fix issue

