function foo(): { property: string } {
    const property = "";
    return {
        property,
    };
}
```


### 🙁 Actual behavior

https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript/assets/7462525/44201e89-badc-48b1-bc71-a459e5a9a348



### 🙂 Expected behavior

When autofix renaming a type property it should consider shorthands and fix appropriately so that it can avoid introducing type errors due to incorrect naming.

```diff
  function foo(): { property: string } {
                    ^^^^^^^^ rename to property2
      const property = "";
      return {
-         property,
+         property2: property,
      };
  }
```

```diff
  function foo(): { property: string } {
      const property = "";
            ^^^^^^^^ rename to property2
      return {
-         property,
+         property: property2,
      };
  }
```

Optionally, it could be extended to be (hugely more complex) for some cases:
```diff
  function foo(): { property: string } {
                    ^^^^^^^^ rename to property2
-     const property = "";
+     const property2 = "";
      return {
-         property,
+         property2,
      };
  }
```

